message.content:
1. There was an objectively determined secondary endpoint.
2. The secondary endpoint was the mean procedure time, skin-to-skin.
3. The mean procedure time favored the OBM group.
4. The mean procedure time for the OBM group was 175 seconds.
5. The mean procedure time for the SBM group was 292 seconds.
6. The difference in mean procedure time between the OBM and SBM groups was statistically significant with a P value less than 0.007.
